quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,52,"And We revealed to Mûsâ (Moses), saying: "
  26,53,"Then Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) sent callers to (all) the cities."
  26,54,"(Saying): "
  27,25,"[As Shaitân (Satan) has barred them from Allâh’s Way] so they do not worship (prostrate themselves before) Allâh, Who brings to light what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knows what you conceal and what you reveal. [Tafsir At-Tabarî]"
  27,26,"Allâh, Lâ ilâha illa Huwa (none has the right to be worshipped but He), the Lord of the Supreme Throne!"
  27,27,"[Sulaimân (Solomon)] said: "